# Python Function Conventions

## Structure

- `src/main.py` — Flask app with `POST /` (Pub/Sub push) and `GET /health`.
- `requirements.txt` for dependencies.
- Dockerfile in function directory; `CMD` uses gunicorn.

## Patterns

```python
MOCK_MODE = os.getenv("MOCK_MODE", "false").lower() == "true"

# Pub/Sub envelope parsing
if envelope.get("message", {}).get("data"):
    job = json.loads(base64.b64decode(raw).decode("utf-8"))
```

## Heavy deps (optional for mock mode)

- F2: `civic-scraper`, `crawl4ai` — fallback heuristics when not installed.
- F3: `docling` — mock text extraction when not installed.

## Shared contracts

Mirror TS schemas in `packages/shared-py/src/beaver_shared/`.
Validate against JSON Schemas in `packages/shared/contracts/` when publishing.

## Async in scraper

Use `asyncio.run()` for aiohttp download logic inside Flask sync handler.
